Text.Value: Open your eyes.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player opens their eyes at enhd of line.

Text.Value: You are more than powerful. An emperor to emperors, your head adorned with a crown of gold, diamond, and ruby.
Not sex. Something far more intoxicating.
Free your mind of her. Let us look forward, never back.
I'll remember you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sweetly and absolutely sincere. She means it.

Text.Value: You are whole. Within and without, free from expectation and the crushing burden of solitude.
You are more than rich - you are the picture of luxury. Your nakedness cloaked in the robes of thrice-combed silk, woven with silver and golden threads.
Leave.
You are sane. Time dances on in sequence, the winding path of time evens, and becomes straight.
Is it not in the illithid's barbarity that we find its splendour?
Desire is instinct, to both mortal and immortal. It's no more disgusting than the mulberry fresh on its bush.
Every step, every breath, every thought shall be - the Minsc-est.
So the critics have said of Faerûn's greatest masterpieces. I'm not so cold-hearted, nor so short-sighted.
No desire is 'peculiar', it is instinct - and instinct never lies.
Safe.
As am I. My thanks are bountiful as your courage.
Free.
I won't forget you. And you won't forget me.
When the hosts of the planes raise their voices in harmony, it is your name they sing, and your grace they seek.
You know illithid are literally incapable of desiring you back?
Contented.
No, really. We're done.
If you seek rapture, find it elsewhere. I can show you but once.
If my innate desires make me disturbing, then I proudly claim the title.
I'm not one to judge, but desiring an extraplanar being like that is peculiar.
Alive.
Sane.
Why should I deny it? My urge is as natural as the grape upon the vine.
No more will you hear the clang of steel on steel. No more will you fear the cry of a wolf, the growl of an ogre. You are warm. You are safe.
You are more than revered - you are worshipped. An epic sung by the bards, a legend known to the scholars. A god among mortals.
Close your eyes. Listen to my voice.
Whole.
You are more than contented - you are at total peace. Your belly is full, your mind rested, your eyes bright.
Powerful.
I offer something rarer than coin -
Minsc.
One moment, forever emblazoned on my memories. I won't soon forget it.
Then be free. You are an eagle, the most divine of messengers, soaring above the peak of Mount Sundabar.
*Her gaze intensifies. Your breath quickens, and your heart skips a beat.*
What did you have in mind?
You know yourself, for such is the beginning of all wisdom. When souls would drink the waters of learning, you are their font.
Thirteen castles, each encircled by thirteen fertile gardens. Platinum coins spill forth from thirteen-and-thirty coffers.
But no tale did justice to its ethereal beauty. It floats like a butterfly, its blood shimmers like silver.
Revered.
Who? Oh yes - Jara. I will miss her coin, it's true. Though perhaps this is not what you meant.
And you'll remember me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sweet and sincere. Not an ounce of arrogance to it.

Text.Value: Oh, I don't need it to desire me back. That's wholly unimportant.
Hells - I'd heard tales of mind flayers. Talons sharp as daggers, and tentacles yet more fearsome.
Your eyes are no less monstrous, I assure you. A lesser woman might be frightened. But I am no lesser woman.
Be well. Be beautiful.
I don't know about this.
The all-being. Here, there is no suffering. Here, you want for nothing. Here, you are anything.
You are the entirety of you. Every path outward leads to adventures yet unknown. Every path inward leads to dreams eternally fulfilled.
You have one word. Tell me: what will you be?
Damn. You're almost as disturbing as the mind flayer.
You are safe. The winds of fate blow you to the warmest of hearths in the most cordial of inns.
The gods themselves cannot grant you my unimaginable bliss. Refuse it once, and you will be left forever wanting.
Shh. Free your mind.
Rich.
At least - take these. May you have at least some comfort in bitter times.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player opens their eyes. Nymph performs a generic "gives a reward" gesture.
EditorData.logicalname: GIVES YOU REWARD - A FEW POTIONS

Text.Value: One word: 'yuck'.
Close your eyes and listen.
*The woman's senses are heightened, and her fires stoked. The mind flayer is no mere curiosity, but an object of desire.*
But perhaps there are other flavours that might satisfy my palate.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sexily. She's making a passionate offer, though not the one the player expects

Text.Value: The creature aroused you, didn't it?
Tell me, then. In a word: what will you be?
Then a part of you remains forever empty, yet keenly felt. An ultimate unknowing, beyond your grasp.
That thing turned you on? Disgusting.
Rapture.
Wise.
With a quiet head, you can once again hear the song of the birds and the wind in the grass. You pluck a flower, and it does not bleed.
That thing could have killed you, and you're musing on its beauty?
I think we're done here.
Show me. Let me know bliss.
You are wise. The erudition of the ages flows through you and from you, illuminating the scholars who seek your counsel.
Close your eyes and listen.
Well, then. I'm glad you're safe.
Er - you are Minsc. You are the most Minsc. Wherever you go, there is only Minsc.
*Your flesh shivers, your heart bursts. True ecstasy, for one fleeting moment.*
I think I'll excuse myself.
I'm afraid I'm not taking new clients.
Show me. Let me know bliss.
You could just give me a few coins instead.
Your seething passions lead only to pleasure. The touch of the sun comforts your flesh, but never burns it.
They are beautiful indeed - and most lethal.
*You see only darkness. Her voice shines through it, warmer than sun yet cooler than night.*
No, really. We're done.
You are alive. Your senses vibrate with sensation - smell, taste, touch, sound, sight. All alert to the beauty of now.
The heavens tremble with the steps of your army. All beasts, all men and women, all creatures of the planes bow to your might.
I'm not interested in sex, but thanks.
Take these. May you have some comfort in bitter times.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Not custom! A generic "gives a reward" gesture.

Text.Value: How could I help it? I don't regret its death. But I marvel that such a work of art could ever live.
Your client is dead. I thought you'd be more upset.
The sound of your heart - your heart - beats a steady rhythm: Hello, hello, hello.
No man or woman, no devil or demon, no goddess or god dares confine you within one border or one creed.

Synopsis: The nymph reacts to having witnessed her lover/client turn to a mind flayer. She can then offer to treat you to an emotional pick-me-upas a reward for saving her.
